This script is made to take backup and restore MySql databases.

How to Use:

1. First you will need edit config.sh file and change DATABASE_NAME, DATABASE_USER etc according to your choice.

2. Run ./backup.sh on terminal, by default it work for one database backup , if you want to take backup of all databases than uncomment line number 11 and comment line 17.

3. If you want to restore you backup, run restore.sh file, but first give correct BACKUP_FILE_PATH in config.sh file

4. For Automatic backup use this script in crontab.
Follow this to run the script using crontab : http://www.thegeekstuff.com/2009/06/15-practical-crontab-examples/
